raceComments: {"comment":"4. RAIKOKE is proving to be very hard to catch. He seems to click well with Damian Lane, who won on him 2 starts back, and returns to the saddle for this assignment. Depending on what version of this fellow turns up, he is the one to beat. 1. REGAL AZMON is a lightly tried 8-year-old gelding with real ability. He ruined his chances when making a slow start fresh up in the Listed Paris Lane Stakes at Flemington nearly 3 weeks ago, but he usually improves with racing, and is worth including in all combinations. 2. APULIA will be resuming from nearly a year off the racetrack. He has won 2 jumpouts this season. He might not be race-fit, but he may not have to be to win a race like this. 7. ENNA'S DREAM may not win often, but she is usually competitive at this level. She is down 5kg from her last start when finishing second. The extra trip will suit here, and she would not be a shock winner.","runners":[4,1,2,7],"exclusive":true}
